Set QCoreApplication applicationVersion so the notification server reports a
version string in org.freedesktop.Notifications.GetServerInformation.

Without this, applicationVersion() is empty and GetServerInformation returns an
empty version field, which some clients (e.g. Chrome) treat as an incomplete
notification server. QS_VERSION is already available via build.hpp, which
main.cpp already includes.

--- a/src/launch/main.cpp
+++ b/src/launch/main.cpp
@@ -111,6 +111,7 @@

 int main(int argc, char** argv) {
 	QCoreApplication::setApplicationName("quickshell");
+	QCoreApplication::setApplicationVersion(QS_VERSION);

 #if CRASH_HANDLER
 	qsCheckCrash(argc, argv);
